  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date, National Aeronautics and Space Administration has obligated $9.5B on federal contracts across 5,863 awards with an average award size of $1.6M. Obligations fell 39.8% year over year. The current-year total is partial; FY26 to date spending sits well below prior full-year totals such as $15B in FY21, $15.2B in FY22, $16.1B in FY23, $15B in FY24, and $15.8B in FY25. Spending in FY2026 to date is concentrated in R&D and space manufacturing: Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences (except Nanotechnology and Biotechnology) accounts for $3.8B, and Guided Missile and Space Vehicle Manufacturing accounts for $1.5B. Engineering Services obligations total $589M and Facilities Support Services total $315M. Major contractors receiving FY2026 to date obligations include CALIFORNIA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY at $1.6B and THE BOEING COMPANY at $813M, followed by THE JOHNS HOPKINS UNIVERSITY APPLIED PHYSICS LABORATORY LLC at $462M and LOCKHEED MARTIN CORP at $377M.",
    "sections": [
