        "heading": "How has NASA's contract spending trended recently?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 39.8% year over year, with FY26 to date obligations totaling $9.5B compared with prior full-year totals such as $15.8B in FY25 and $16.1B in FY23. The FY26 total is a partial fiscal-year figure and follows a multi-year range between $15B and $16.1B from FY21 through FY25."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What are NASA's primary purchases and who receives the most funding?",
        "body": "Research and development dominates FY2026 to date obligations, led by Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences (except Nanotechnology and Biotechnology) at $3.8B and related R&D categories totaling $583M and $342M. Manufacturing and services categories include Guided Missile and Space Vehicle Manufacturing at $1.5B, Engineering Services at $589M, and Facilities Support Services at $315M; top vendors include CALIFORNIA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY at $1.6B and THE BOEING COMPANY at $813M."
      }
